<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-614-048  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 614 048.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: automatic word processing translator for e-mail.andO;(Keyword Office Technologies Ltd.'s KeyPak bundled with ConsumersSoftware Inc.'s Network Courier)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Consumers Software Inc. (marketing)Keyword Office Technologies Ltd. (marketing).andO;Product:   KEYpak (Data conversion software) (marketing)Network Courier (Office automation software) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersBundled SoftwareMarketing Strategy.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: Automatic Word Processing Translator For E-Mail VANCOUVER,BRITISH COLUMBIA, CANADA, 1990 MAY 11 (NB) -- Consumers Software here andKeyword Office Technologies of Calgary, Alberta, have bundled their productsto provide an electronic mail facility that translates documents from oneword processor format to another automatically.andM;The Network CourierPak integrates Keyword's KeyPak document interchangesoftware with Consumers' Network Courier electronic mail software forlocal-area networks.andP;  For US$2,490, users will get the Network Couriersoftware for one network server, with document translation format for threeword processors.andM;Buyers can choose whichever formats they want from a list of 32, said Keywordspokeswoman Louise Gallagher.andP;  The list includes major PC word processors aswell as some mainframe word processor formats and print file formats,Gallagher told Newsbytes.andM;Additional formats are available at three for US$500, said Michael Shandrick,spokesman for Consumers Software.andM;Each e-mail user sets the software to translate incoming documents to apreferred word processor format.andP;  Users send documents in their own format,and the files are translated automatically to the recipients preferred formatas they are sent.andM;Current users of Network Courier can buy KeyPak separately and integrate itwith their e-mail software, Gallagher said.andM;Both Keyword and Consumers will sell the software combination.andM;(Grant Buckler/19900511/Press Contact: Michael Shandrick, Consumers Software,604-688-4548; Louise Gallagher, Keyword Office Technologies, 403-250-1770)</TEXT></DOC>